🎯 The 3-state system (lock this)
🟢 GREEN — Valid (Executable)
Topology complete
All invariants satisfied
✔ Run enabled
✔ Deterministic results
✔ No warnings
🟠 ORANGE — Incomplete (Authoring)
Engineering intent not finished

Typical cases:

INTER_ROOM with no adjacent room yet
Missing reciprocal segment
Geometry entered but no segments yet
❌ Run disabled
⚠ Guidance shown
✔ UI remains calm (no “error” tone)
🔴 RED — Invalid (Broken)
Model violates physical / logical rules

Examples:

Self-adjacency
Invalid room reference
Negative length
EXTERNAL with adjacent_room_id
❌ Run blocked
❌ Explicit errors shown
🚨 Requires correction
🧠 The key principle (this is gold)
GREEN  = executable
ORANGE = incomplete intent
RED    = invalid model

GREEN   → Run button ENABLED + green
ORANGE  → disabled (grey)
RED     → disabled (grey)
NO TOPOLOGY → disabled (grey)
